title: SpaceX launches second Axiom Space private astronaut mission to ISS
summary: Axiom Space’s second private astronaut mission is on its way to the International Space Station after a launch May 21.

title: NASA seeks to shore up congressional support for Artemis
summary: As NASA faces both short-term and long-term uncertainty about its funding, the agency is turning to its most powerful advocates: its astronauts.

title: EarthDaily Analytics offers VENµS imagery access
summary: Vancouver-based EarthDaily Analytics is offering access to the French-Israeli Vegetation and Environment monitoring on a New Micro-Satellite (VENµS) mission through Amazon Web Services.

title: Iceye to supply UAE SAR satellites
summary: Iceye plans to develop a five-satellite constellation for Bayanat, a United Arab Emirates geospatial analysis firm, and Emirati fleet operator Yahsat.

title: Planet seeks partners that can extract more value from data
summary: Planet is working with partners to “get value out of our data,” said Kevin Weil, Planet’s president of product and business.
